explanation: The inner loop used 'for j in range(i):', so for each pair (i,j) it only checked whether the earlier item j dominates the later item i. That misses cases where the later item dominates the earlier one. I changed the inner loop to iterate over all j (for j in range(n):) so both orders of each pair are considered. Self-comparisons cannot trigger a match because the strict part of the condition prevents equality from passing.
